reviews.text: Best pizza and Italian food for delivery around! We have pretty much never had a bad meal from them and order almost once a week! Good portions, usually get at least two meals out of our order. Call and order directly, the staff is great, and the customer service is great, not like using the delivery app middlemen that don't care about service at all!

The guy answering the phones needs to take customer service classes. Lied about delivery window. Took well over an hour and half. Lied about the food leaving the restaurant when it wasn‚Äôt even made. And Screwed up my order. Literally he screws up my order every time i order. Need to speak to owner because the Julio character is beyond disrespectful.

I was stuck at the airport today picking up my kid, and because of the multiple storms, I was waiting since 4pm. I placed an order for a pie thinking I'd definitely be able to pick it up by 10:30 (close). Wrong. I called and explained I'd be late, a guy & gal I spoke to went above and beyond to help make sure I got my order even after closing. Even called me back to tell me what they'd do. Pizza was great, but I inhaled it cold, need to go back for fresh pizza, but I can say for sure  customer service is TOP TIER.

Our favorite pizza place in Stamford. We have actually never been to the restaurant as we always find it easy to order it home. They have been amazing every time and the service is great too. Toppings anyone can make, but the bread is what counts. Their base is extremely soft and crispy at the same time and they taste great even on the next day!

Amazing experience introduced to me by my late friend Diane who had me try the Broccoli Rabe with Orecchiette Pasta and I have been hooked ever since and no one does it like Westover's; hope they rename it the Diane's Special üòâ. S I P my friend üôèüíñ.

detailedReviews.author: Christine Towle
detailedReviews.text: Me and family were visiting Stamford and came across Westover Pizza - we tried a couple pizzas, a calzone, an Italian sub, soup, and their Italian ice. The pizzas were good, the sub, calzone, and Italian ice were AMAZING, and the soup, pasta fagioli, wasn't to my liking. I definitely recommend this place. They are quick and clean, and the staff is friendly and competent. I haven't had real Italian ice in so long, it was a nice treat.
